{"body": "> That may be an argument for rejecting a feature request, but not for introducing a breaking change.\r\n\r\nYes, it is an argument to introducing a breaking change too for two reasons:\r\n\r\n1. Rails Core don't want to maintain this feature in the future. The behavior introduced by this feature is not worth the maintenance cost or the doubts that it can introduce for the users like the examples @senny added in the last comment. \r\n2. Rails 4 was a major release so breaking changes are expected and it was the best moment to remove code that doesn't fit the direction the framework is taking or doesn't seems a good API.", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/22895299", "created_at": "2013-08-19T18:51:36Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/9683#issuecomment-22895299", "updated_at": "2013-08-19T18:51:36Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 9683, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/rafaelfranca/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/rafaelfranca/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/rafaelfranca/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/rafaelfranca", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/rafaelfranca/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/rafaelfranca", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/rafaelfranca/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://0.gravatar.com/avatar/0525b332aafb83307b32d9747a93de03?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F2c7b84fa30f0cea96a90729afe2970a0.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/rafaelfranca/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/rafaelfranca/received_events", "gravatar_id": "0525b332aafb83307b32d9747a93de03", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/rafaelfranca/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "rafaelfranca", "type": "User", "id": 47848, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/rafaelfranca/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "